<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
[[ Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B5B5DA52-81E9-40A9-ABF4-20FEC823A808" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Characidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Characidium Reinhardt 1867:55" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Characidium Reinhardt</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
This new species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B5B5DA52-81E9-40A9-ABF4-20FEC823A808" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Characidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Characidium Reinhardt 1867:55" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Characidium Reinhardt, 1867</taxonomicName>
, brings the total for the genus to about 50 valid species (Buckup, 2003). All are small fishes, ranging from about 20 to 80 mm SL, and are usually associated with moving water, often in riffle habitats, similar to most North American darter species of the family Percidae. They are members of the family 
<taxonomicName family="Crenuchidae" pageNumber="2" rank="family">Crenuchidae</taxonomicName>
, the monophyly of which was recently established by Buckup (1993b, 1998), who also established the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B5B5DA52-81E9-40A9-ABF4-20FEC823A808" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Characidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Characidium Reinhardt 1867:55" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Characidium</taxonomicName>
, although this is supported only by one synapomorphy: a black spot near base of middle caudal fin rays, which is sometimes secondarily lost or modified. Their known distributions extend from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Panamá">Panama</normalizedToken>
to Argentina. In his review of the family, Buckup (1993a) examined material of this species and all other Venezuelan species available for study, and described several new genera and species: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:49687BED-58F5-4FA5-A810-0F0FC49F1AAE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Leptocharacidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Leptocharacidium omospilus Buckup 1993:103" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omospilum">Leptocharacidium omospilum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EBBF1BA7-F2E4-451C-990D-37DE8B63E42E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Ammocryptocharax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ammocryptocharax minutus Buckup 1993:109" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minutus">Ammocryptocharax minutus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:55FF4139-38F6-4C20-80A0-31E602D3F34E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Melanocharacidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Melanocharacidium compressus Buckup 1993:114" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="compressus">Melanocharacidium compressus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:29D9CDC4-C482-4CB8-BE77-2334C9020C99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Melanocharacidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Melanocharacidium dispilomma Buckup 1993:120" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dispilomma">M. dispilomma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DABE35C3-B488-40B1-A6B2-0FBE64964802" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Melanocharacidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Melanocharacidium melanopteron Buckup 1993:125" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopteron">M. melanopteron</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Odontocharacidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aphanes">Odontocharacidium aphanes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7478EF34-968F-4E74-9F24-24F63B5C293B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Microcharacidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microcharacidium gnomus Buckup 1993:137" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">Microcharacidium gnomus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:683F3938-9EC0-41BE-82EE-C04DFD8A18B9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Microcharacidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microcharacidium weitzmani Buckup 1993:141" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="weitzmani">Microcharacidium weitzmani</taxonomicName>
. Since this review, no one has worked with the numerous other undescribed Venezuelan species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
